organization.description: The Federal Laboratory Consortium for Technology Transfer (FLC) is the nationwide network of federal laboratories that provides the forum to develop strategies and opportunities for linking laboratory mission technologies and expertise with the marketplace.
organization.title: Federal Laboratory Consortium
organization.name: federal-laboratory-consortium

name: human-factors-lab
notes: Human factors research and development capabilities in all modes of transportation. Studies relationships between humans and automation technologies to improve safety, security, and productivity with due concern for unintended consequences. The FRA encourages railroad stakeholders outside of the Federal government (including academia and industry) to utilize the CTIL facility. FRA funds the Volpe Center to provide research and technical support to anyone working on an FRA-approved project in the CTIL lab. Volpe reserves the right to restrict access to laboratory facilities, equipment and personnel at its discretion based on priorities, current use and/or need. External use requires a formal agreement governming usage terms and conditions. As a non-appropriated organization, reimbursement for costs directly associated with the use of Volpe laboratory equipment, facilities and/or attendent staff is required.

extras.value: Conduct experiments in which the human operator (i.e. locomotive engineer or vehicle drivers) run through simulated scenarios. We can manipulate many aspects of their experience (e.g. weather, warning signal aspects, signage, mechanical problems) to create an experimental scenario and collect a wide variety of human performance metrics for subsequent analysis.

title: Human Factors Lab
